{"key":"post-12531361","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12531361</id>\n<content>Just rinse out the glovebox with plain water, or if you wish, use soap and water.&amp;nbsp; Cleaning chemicals, especially volatile ones are not necessary.&amp;nbsp; You won't be laying your spores, spawn, or substrates in contact with the glovebox, and it will stop air currents in the room whether it's been sanitized or not.&amp;nbsp; Always flame outside the box regardless.&amp;nbsp; A flame in a glovebox will heat it up inside and lead to condensation, preventing you from seeing what you're doing.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12531526</next>\n<prev>12531344</prev>\n<first>12531055</first>\n<last>12531599</last>\n<when>1273426921</when>\n<utime>05/09/10 08:42 PM</utime>\n</post>"}